<h1>HOWTO: Installing SQLDeveloper</h1>


<table border="1" cellpadding="20">
	 <tr>
		 <th> Platform </th> <th> name of package </th> <th> Notes </th>
	 </tr>
	 <tr>
		 <td> Windows 32-bit (no JRE) </td>
		 <td> <a href="http://www.csit.parkland.edu/~cschultz/csc191/resources/sqldeveloper-2.1.1.64.45-no-jre.zip"> sqldeveloper-2.1.1.64.45-no-jre.zip</a> </td>
		  <td> To install and run:
			  <ul>
				  <li>Ensure you have a JDK installed, if not, download <a href="http://java.sun.com/j2se/1.5.0/download.jsp">here</a> <br>
				  (click the Download for JDK 6 Update <b><i>xx</i></b>, where <b><i>xx</i></b> is the latest update)
				   <li> Extract sqldeveloper.zip into any folder, using folder names
				   <li> Within that folder, open the sqldeveloper folder
				   <li> Double-click sqldeveloper.exe
			   </ul>
		   </td>
	   </tr>
	   <tr>
		 <td> Windows 32-bit </td>
		   <td> <a href="http://www.csit.parkland.edu/~cschultz/csc191/resources/sqldeveloper-2.1.1.64.45.zip"> sqldeveloper-2.1.1.64.45.zip</a> </td>
		    <td>  To install and run:
                              <ul>
                   <li> Extract sqldeveloper.zip into any folder, using folder names
                   <li> Within that folder, open the sqldeveloper folder
                   <li> Double-click sqldeveloper.exe
                 </ul>
               </td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
	  <td> Windows 64-bit (no JRE) </td>
	  <td> <a href="http://www.csit.parkland.edu/~cschultz/csc191/resources/sqldeveloper64-2.1.1.64.45-no-jre.zip">sqldeveloper64-2.1.1.64.45-no-jre.zip</a> </td>
		  <td> To install and run:
			  <ul>
				  <li>Ensure you have a JDK installed, if not, download <a href="http://java.sun.com/j2se/1.5.0/download.jsp">here</a> <br>
				  (click the Download for JDK 6 Update <b><i>xx</i></b>, where <b><i>xx</i></b> is the latest update)
				   <li> Extract sqldeveloper.zip into any folder, using folder names
				   <li> Within that folder, open the sqldeveloper folder
				   <li> Double-click sqldeveloper.exe
			   </ul>
		   </td>
	   </tr>
  <tr>
	  <td> Mac OS X </td>
	  <td> <a href="http://www.csit.parkland.edu/~cschultz/csc191/resources/sqldeveloper-3.0.04.34-macosx.tar.gz">sqldeveloper-3.0.04.34-macosx.tar.gz</a> </td>
		  <td> To install and run:
			  <ul>
				  <li>Ensure you have a JDK installed, if not, download <a href="http://developer.apple.com/java/download/">here</a> <br>
				  (click the Download for JDK 6 Update <b><i>xx</i></b>, where <b><i>xx</i></b> is the latest update)
				   <li> Double-click the sqldeveloper icon
			   </ul>
		   </td>
	   </tr>

  <tr>
	  <td> Linux </td>
	  <td> <a href="http://www.csit.parkland.edu/~cschultz/csc191/resources/sqldeveloper-3.0.04.34-1.noarch.rpm">sqldeveloper-3.0.04.34-1.noarch.rpm</a> </td>
		  <td> To install and run:
			  <ul>
				  <li>Ensure you have a JDK installed, if not, download <a href="http://java.sun.com/j2se/1.5.0/download.jsp">here</a> <br>
				  (click the Download for JDK 6 Update <b><i>xx</i></b>, where <b><i>xx</i></b> is the latest update)
				  <li>rpm -Uhv sqldeveloper-3.0.04.34-1.noarch.rpm 
				  <li>cd sqldeveloper - sqldeveloper
			   </ul>
		   </td>
